Package ooassignment3.fueltypeclasses

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FuelTypeInterface
    This is the interface version of fuel type, allowing for classes that use different default implementations than the ones provided in the abstract class variant.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Diesel
    This class represents the diesel fuel type.
    Electric
    This class represents the electric engine fuel type.
    FuelTypeAbstract
    This abstract class is the parent class of all concrete fuel types that don't directly use the FuelTypeInterface.
    Hybrid
    This class represents the hybrid engine fuel type.
    Petrol
    This class represents the petrol fuel type.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    FuelTypeEnum
    The enum representing the possible fuel types.
